---
title: Dad’s Grilled Lemon-Chicken Caesar Salad with Croutons & Parmesan
description: If the dad in your life loves a quick, delicious dinner, this grilled salad is right up his alley. After just a minute or two on a hot grill, lettuce turns smoky and savory without wilting. You’ll chop it and toss with a creamy, lemony Caesar dressing—the perfect bed for the juicy, lemony grilled chicken. In fact, you may never leave your Caesar salad un-grilled again!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66313b429eb2c19a07b9679a-a5b26a50.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66313b429eb2c19a07b9679a-en-US.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 19 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 690 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/dads-grilled-lemon-chicken-caesar-salad-66313b429eb2c19a07b9679a
cuisine: North America
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
---

Preheat a well-oiled #grill{} to medium heat.

> If using a grill pan, you'll heat it in Step 2.

Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @baby lettuce{2} lengthwise,
keeping the root intact.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large
pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until about
1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add chicken to grill (or #grill pan{}); grill until cooked through and lightly
charred, ~{3-5%minutes} per side (grills can vary). Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Squeeze one lemon wedge over chicken.

> GRILL PAN ALTERNATIVE: Heat a well-oiled grill pan over medium-high heat.
> Cook as instructed.

Increase heat to high. Add lettuce, cut sides down, to grill; grill,
undisturbed, until charred, ~{30-90%seconds} (grills can vary). Transfer to a
cutting board, grilled sides up.

> Skip grilling lettuce if using a grill pan—it'll taste just as great fresh!

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Caesar dressing{3%oz} and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Once cool enough to handle, trim and discard root end from lettuce; chop into
bite-size pieces.

Transfer lettuce to a #large bowl{}. Toss with as much dressing as you like;
taste and season with salt and pepper. Add more lemon juice if desired.

Slice chicken crosswise. Lightly crush @croutons{1} in their bag.

Divide salad between plates. Top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon},
croutons, and chicken. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.